Definition at line 451 of file lov_cl_internal.h.

loff_t lov_io::lis_io_endpos

Original end-of-io position for this IO, set by the upper layer as cl_io::u::ci_rw::pos + cl_io::u::ci_rw::count.

lov remembers this, changes pos and count to fit IO into a single stripe and uses saved value to determine when IO iterations have to stop.

This is used only for CIT_READ and CIT_WRITE io's.
